OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1771909410
OL,3,CLord Mandelson released on bail
OL,4,Cpending further investigation
OL,6,FThe UK Government will consider
OL,7,Fintroducing such legislation once
OL,8,Fpolice have finished their
OL,9,Finvestigation into the King's
OL,10,Fdisgraced brother, the Press
OL,11,FAssociation understands.
OL,13,FThe Lib Dems will table a humble
OL,14,Faddress in the Commons ` the same
OL,15,Farcane mechanism the Tories used to
OL,16,Fpress for the release of files on Lord
OL,17,FMandelson's appointment as ambassador
OL,18,F` in a bid to compel the Government to
OL,19,Fdisclose information about Andrew, who
OL,20,Fserved as a trade envoy between 2001
OL,21,Fand 2011.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
